Class MapSheetsGrid

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gvsig.tools.dispose.impl.AbstractDisposable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Projected, ExtendedPropertiesSupport, FLayer, FLayerHidesArea, LayerListener, Classifiable, ClassifiableVectorial, InfoByPoint, SingleLayer, VectorLayer, LegendContentsChangedListener, ILabelable, IMapSheetsIdentified, Metadata, Disposable, DynObject, Observer, Persistent

    public class MapSheetsGrid
extends FLyrVect
implements IMapSheetsIdentified
    This subclass of FLyrVect is used to handle the map sheets grid when it's not being adjusted. The draw method only acts when this grid is not active as grid and being adjusted.

      • cloneLayer

        public FLayer cloneLayer()
        Description copied from interface: FLayer

        This method can be used to have a fast cloned layer.

        The implementations should take care of not recreate this layer. Instead of this, is better to use the same source (driver) and deepclone the legend. Exception: the labels aren't deepcloned to avoid memory consumption.

        Note: Labels are memory consuming to speed up layers like PostGIS and so on.

        Specified by:
        cloneLayer in interface FLayer
        Overrides:
        cloneLayer in class FLyrVect
        Returns:
        a layer that is a clonation of this layer

        Specified by:

        Overrides:
